    "summary": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Assuming that a claim is true because it has not been or cannot be proven false, or vice versa.",
        "spans": []
      }
    ],
    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "An appeal to ignorance is an argument for a conclusion based on a lack of evidence. There are two forms of the argument depending on whether the argument is affirmative or negative:",
